"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 570px; height: 192px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Depiction of the enzymatic defect in 5-aminolevulinic acid (ALA) dehydratase porphyria (ADP). This disorder is characterized by a defect in the enzyme ALA dehydratase (ALAD), leading to the accumulation and excretion of ALA. The reduced production of heme also contributes via loss of heme-mediated repression of ALA synthase (ALAS), the enzyme that promotes the formation of ALA from glycine and succinyl CoA.",
